# GoogleCalendarClone2025
This Google Calendar clone is the capstone project for my Software Development, Frontend Specialization course through CourseCareers
The goal of this project was independently code all the logic necessary for a useable calendar including but not limited to: creating, editing, deleting events. An SDD (software design document) was provided, listing all necessary features and providing images to match in styling.
This project should function as a legitimate replacement for a personal calendar, as it stores your data in localStorage, and will "remember" your previous data when used on the same device


## **_ INSTRUCTIONS FOR SETTING UP PROJECT_**
### Instruction assume that you already have (a) an account set up with a coding editor, preferably VSC, (b) node.js and git installed, and set up in your editor

First clone this project from my account, if you have not already done so.

1.  Click the green button that says "Code"

2.  From the Local tab, select the HTTPS option (these should be the default)

3.  Copy the github link provided

### Open VSC, or your editor (if you use another editor/terminal your cmds syntax may differ slightly)
### In the terminal (powershell) run these commands, in order

0. A. (if you haven't already cloned into the project) run "git clone XYZ" where XYZ is the copied github link
1. B. Once cloned into project, assure that you are cd'ed into the folder "GoogleCalendarClone2025"

2. "npm i"

3. "npm run dev"

